label: Da Vinci v9
overview:
The Da Vinci wall controller is a Multi Chanel Z-Wave device that contains up to 6 relays and up to 9 touch buttons that can be set to control either the relays (On/Off switches and shutters) or any other on/off (SWITCH_BINARY) , shutter (MULTILEVEL_SWITCH) Z-Wave device.

Double Press the following buttons in the following order 8,1,3. Use the reset procedure only when the primary controller is missing or inoperable.

parameters.label: Button 1 Type
parameters.overview:
1 = switch on/off

2 = blind up

3 = blind down

4 = switch multiway

5 = blind-up multiway

6 = blind-down multiway

parameters.label: Button 1 Partner-Id
parameters.overview:
• When setting Button (EP) to blind, Partner Id EP also change to blind (opposite direction).
  • Blind must contain Partner Id which is different than 0 and it must be unique. 
  • When setting blind to switch, Partner Id also change to switch

parameters.label: Button 1 Output
parameters.overview: Output = Relay

parameters.label: Button 1 attributes
parameters.overview:
Bit [0] = LED enable

Bit [1] = Sound enable

Bit [2] = Dry contact enable

Bit [3] = Motor enable

parameters.label: Device Toggle or Pulse the output
parameters.description: Device Toggle or Pulse the output
parameters.overview:
Device Toggle or Pulse the output:

0 = Toggle

1 = Pulse

parameters.label: Device Background LEDs Timeout
parameters.overview:
Device Background LEDs Timeout:

0 = always Off

10 - 40 = Timeout in seconds

255 = always On!!!!!!!

parameters.label: Device touch sensitivity
parameters.overview:
You can choose value between 0 – 7

0 = most sensitive

7 = least sensitive

parameters.label: Save and Reset
parameters.overview: 255 = save and reset
